<section class=\"mbr-section article mbr-section__container\" id=\"content1-27\" style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 0px;\">

    <div class=\"container\">
        <div class=\"row\">
            <div class=\"col-xs-12 lead\"><p>Glovtex Oil &amp; Gas Limited develop and implemented a Quality Management System (QMS) in order to document the company’s basic policies and processes, to better satisfy the requirements and expectations of its customers and to continually improve quality through the use of the QMS.</p><p>The QMS meets the requirements of the international Standard ISO 9001:2008. This system addresses the design and production of the company’s products and services.</p><p><br></p></div>
        </div>
    </div>

</section>

<section class=\"mbr-section article mbr-section__container\" id=\"content2-28\" style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px;\">

    <div class=\"container\">
        <div class=\"row\">
            <div class=\"col-xs-12 lead\"><blockquote>-\tTo ensure strict compliance with contractual requirement / client specification and relevant international codes and standards.</blockquote><blockquote>-\tTo support quality improvement, cost effectiveness, reliability, efficiency, safety and security throughout the project life span.</blockquote><blockquote>-\tTo ensure prompt completion and delivery of a “dear-to-hear” project which meet the stringent quality requirement by our client within the given time limit.</blockquote><blockquote>-\tTo establish system of quality Control Audit with a view to reduce to barest minimum, the frequency of non-conformities in our services or products.</blockquote><blockquote>-\tTo ensure application of relevant engineering data for supplies, construction, assembling and inspection at every stage of the work from start to finish until transfer of facilities to client.</blockquote><blockquote>-\tTo ensure that all records relating to project are readily available for easy reference at all time. In line with this, a complete dossier of As-Built file materials and inspection certificates, project completion and acceptance certificates etc shall be maintained and available to client when required.</blockquote></div>
        </div>
    </div>

</section>

